sentences: Gioúri Melikov (Greek: Γιούρι Μελίκοβ, Russian: Юрий Меликов; born 1997) is a Cypriot singer and songwriter.
He launched his musical career in 2014 as a contestant of The Voice of Greece, season 1.
In 2015, Melikov entered the Eurovision Song Project (the Cypriot national selections for Eurovision Song Contest 2015) with his song "Victorious".
Yuri Melikov was born in 1997 in Paralimni, the son of an Armenian father and a Russian-Cypriot mother.

sentences: On 23 April 2014, Melikov said that he is in a relationship with a girl named Valentina, and that he dedicated a song to her during the semi-finals of The Voice of Greece.
He was raised in Paralimni and his mother enrolled him in a conservatory, where he took classical and modern music lessons for six years.
This was after his mother suggested him that he take music lessons because he listens to music all day yet she doesn't hear him sing.
